result.execSummary:
All charges against Willie Davis in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Willie Davis is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Willie Davis not in court, in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The state of Mississippi has not issued a governor's warrant on this case.  On motion of defense, court dismissed the case.
Criminal Warrant for Commitment, signed and filed.

Defendant Willie Davis in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Willie Davis in custody.  Anthony J Moore appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   All parties appeared by video conference.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28
Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Tennessee.
Defendant contested extradition.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
  Per Chief Judge Directive 22-04 effective June 13, 2022, this calendar will be assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.  Status conference scheduled for June 24, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
